## 6. Security Best Practices

### 6.1 Input Validation

**Always validate user input:**
```typescript
import { z } from 'zod'

const emailSchema = z.string().email()
const passwordSchema = z.string().min(8).max(100)

// Validate before sending to backend
const result = emailSchema.safeParse(userInput)
if (!result.success) {
  // Show error to user
}
```

**Why client-side validation:**
- Immediate user feedback
- Reduce unnecessary API calls
- **Not a replacement for backend validation** (defense in depth)

---

### 6.2 Sensitive Data in Logs

**Forbidden:**
```typescript
// ❌ NEVER log sensitive data
console.log('User logged in:', { email, password })
console.log('Auth token:', token)
console.log('User SSN:', user.ssn)
```

**Allowed:**
```typescript
// ✅ Log non-sensitive context
console.log('User logged in:', { userId: user.id })
console.log('Auth check: token present =', !!token)
```

**Rule:** Never log PII, tokens, passwords, or secrets.

---

### 6.3 Error Messages

**Forbidden:**
```typescript
// ❌ Reveals internal details
throw new Error('Database connection failed: postgres://...')
throw new Error('SQL error: SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ...')
```

**Allowed:**
```typescript
// ✅ Generic, user-friendly
throw new Error('Unable to log in. Please try again.')
```

**Backend logs detailed errors, frontend shows generic messages.**

---

### 6.4 OWASP Mobile Top 10 Compliance

Checklist for v1:

- [x] **M1: Improper Platform Usage** — Use SecureStore, not AsyncStorage
- [ ] **M2: Insecure Data Storage** — Mobile: encrypted (SecureStore ✅) / Web: localStorage (XSS-vulnerable, INV-21 → HTTP-only cookies)
- [x] **M3: Insecure Communication** — HTTPS only (enforced by backend)
- [ ] **M4: Insecure Authentication** — Implement token expiration, refresh
- [ ] **M5: Insufficient Cryptography** — Use platform crypto (SecureStore handles)
- [x] **M6: Insecure Authorization** — Protected routes, auth guards
- [ ] **M7: Client Code Quality** — ESLint, TypeScript strict mode
- [ ] **M8: Code Tampering** — (Future: code signing, obfuscation)
- [ ] **M9: Reverse Engineering** — (Future: ProGuard on Android)
- [ ] **M10: Extraneous Functionality** — No debug code in production builds

