## 9. Security Checklist

Before production:

- [ ] Tokens stored in SecureStore (mobile) or HTTP-only cookies (web)
- [ ] No secrets in source code or environment files
- [ ] HTTPS enforced for all API requests
- [ ] Token expiration and refresh implemented
- [ ] Auth guards on protected routes
- [ ] Input validation on all forms
- [ ] No PII in logs or error messages
- [ ] CSP headers configured (web)
- [ ] Deep link handlers validate tokens
- [ ] Logout clears all tokens
- [ ] Session timeout implemented
- [ ] Error messages are user-friendly, not revealing

---

## 10. Forbidden Patterns

❌ **DO NOT:**

- Store tokens in AsyncStorage
- Store passwords anywhere (even encrypted)
- Log sensitive data (PII, tokens, passwords)
- Show detailed error messages to users
- Skip token validation on protected routes
- Hardcode API keys or secrets
- Use weak password requirements
- Trust client-side validation alone (always validate backend too)

---

## Summary

**Authentication flow:**
1. Login → Receive tokens → Store in SecureStore/cookies
2. Attach token to GraphQL requests (URQL auth exchange)
3. Refresh token when expired
4. Logout → Clear tokens + call backend

**Security posture:**
- Platform-appropriate storage (iOS Keychain, Android Keystore, HTTP-only cookies)
- Defense in depth (client + backend validation)
- No secrets in repo
- OWASP Mobile Top 10 compliance
- User-friendly error messages

